Doop - Framework for Java Pointer Analysis
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Authors
   * Martin Bravenboer <martin.bravenboer@acm.org>
   * Yannis Smaragdakis <>

License
  MIT license (see LICENSE)

Installation
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  LogicBlox
  ------------

  The LogicBlox engine needs to be installed. Set the environment
  variable LOGICBLOX_HOME. The 'run' script if Doop will take care of
  setting additional environment variables, such as PATH and
  LD_LIBRARY_PATH.

  Java
  ------------

  If you want to run the testsuite, then you need to download jre1.3
  (or edit the script to use a different version). Also, for
  experiments in general it is useful to have different Java versions
  installed. It does not matter which platform you install: only the
  jar archives are used.

  Suggested download link:
   http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/archive-139210.html

  Configure your Java installations in doop.conf. The default
  configuration assumes you install the JRE versions in the
  subdirectory 'externals'.

  For example, after downloading the jre1.3 to your Desktop:

  $ cd externals
  $ chmod u+x ~/Desktop/j2re-1_3_1_20-linux-i586.bin
  $ ~/Desktop/j2re-1_3_1_20-linux-i586.bin

  DaCapo Benchmarks
  -----------------

  If you want to run the DaCapo benchmarks, then you need to download
  the DaCapo distribution separately.

  $ cd externals
  $ wget http://voxel.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/dacapobench/dacapo-2006-10-MR2-xdeps.zip

  The command ./compile-tests (explained next) will unpack the
  distribution. If you did not download the distribution, this script
  will print instructions.

Examples
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Run a test by hand:

      $ ./compile-tests
      $ ./run context-insensitive jars/jre1.3/tests/hello/Empty.jar
        (database will be linked at last-analysis)

      Or, using a specific JRE:

      $ ./run -jre1.3 context-insensitive jars/jre1.3/tests/hello/Empty.jar

  Run a dacapo benchmark:

      $ ./compile-tests
      $ ./run -jre1.4 context-insensitive jars/dacapo/antlr.jar

      To run a DaCapo benchmark, you need to download the benchmark
      suite to the subdirectory 'externals'. See the instructions
      printed at the end of the 'compile-tests' script.

  Run all tests:

      $ ./compile-tests
      $ ./run-testsuites

      To run all tesuites, you will need jre1.3. jre1.4, jre1.5 and
      jre1.6.

      For a basic run of the testsuites, you need only jre1.3.

      $ ./run-testsuites basic

Dependencies
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Included in the binary distribution of Doop:

  * Soot 2.3.0 (LGPL)
  * soot-fact-generation (MIT)
  * logicblox-unit (MIT)
  * jsglr (LGPL)

Not included:

  * LogicBlox engine (commercial license)

  * Dacapo benchmark (xdeps edition)
    - please download to externals subdir
